<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c73">As a heavy AI-assisted open source code creator (and someone with 40+ years of dev experience), this seems wrong-headed to me. I think it is an excellent policy, as they say, to &quot;value contributors over their contributions,&quot; but this policy excludes all potential contributors who use the latest tools. It will eventually doom zig to a smaller &quot;artisanal&quot; pool of contributors, rather than welcoming newbies and helping them become better open-source developers.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=47961113&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D47957294%2347961113" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr class="athing comtr" id="47961302"><td><table border="0"><tr><td class="ind" indent="1"><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="40"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks"><center><a id='up_47961302' href='vote?id=47961302&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D47957294'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=faitswulff" class="hnuser">faitswulff</a> <span class="age" title="2026-04-30T12:15:05 1777551305"><a href="item?id=47961302">4 hours ago</a></span> <span id="unv_47961302"></span><span class="navs"> | <a href="#47961113" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">parent</a> | <a href="#47962760" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">next</a> <a class="togg clicky" id="47961302" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)">[–]</a><span class="onstory"></span></span></span></div><br>
